.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxFileDialog() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBdestroy(This :: wxFileDialog()) -> ok.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Destroys the object


.RE
.B
\fBgetDirectory(This) -> unicode:charlist()\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxFileDialog().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the default directory.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFilename(This) -> unicode:charlist()\fR
\fB                     when This :: wxFileDialog().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the default filename.

.PP
Note: This function can't be used with dialogs which have the \fIwxFD_MULTIPLE\fR style, use \fIgetFilenames/1\fR instead.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFilenames(This) -> [unicode:charlist()]\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxFileDialog().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Fills the array \fIfilenames\fR with the names of the files chosen.

.PP
This function should only be used with the dialogs which have \fIwxFD_MULTIPLE\fR style, use \fIgetFilename/1\fR for the others.

.PP
Note that under Windows, if the user selects shortcuts, the filenames include paths, since the application cannot determine the full path of each referenced file by appending the directory containing the shortcuts to the filename.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFilterIndex(This) -> integer() when This :: wxFileDialog().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the index into the list of filters supplied, optionally, in the wildcard parameter.

.PP
Before the dialog is shown, this is the index which will be used when the dialog is first displayed.

.PP
After the dialog is shown, this is the index selected by the user.


.RE
.B
\fBgetMessage(This) -> unicode:charlist() when This :: wxFileDialog().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the message that will be displayed on the dialog.


.RE
.B
\fBgetPath(This) -> unicode:charlist() when This :: wxFileDialog().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the full path (directory and filename) of the selected file.

.PP
Note: This function can't be used with dialogs which have the \fIwxFD_MULTIPLE\fR style, use \fIgetPaths/1\fR instead.


.RE
.B
\fBgetPaths(This) -> [unicode:charlist()] when This :: wxFileDialog().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Fills the array \fIpaths\fR with the full paths of the files chosen.

.PP
This function should only be used with the dialogs which have \fIwxFD_MULTIPLE\fR style, use \fIgetPath/1\fR for the others.


.RE
.B
\fBgetWildcard(This) -> unicode:charlist()\fR
\fB                     when This :: wxFileDialog().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the file dialog wildcard.


.RE
.B
\fBnew(Parent, [Option]) -> wxFileDialog()\fR
\fB             when\fR
\fB                 Parent :: wxWindow:wxWindow(),\fR
\fB                 Option ::\fR
\fB                     {message, unicode:chardata()} |\fR
\fB                     {defaultDir, unicode:chardata()} |\fR
\fB                     {defaultFile, unicode:chardata()} |\fR
\fB                     {wildCard, unicode:chardata()} |\fR
\fB                     {style, integer()} |\fR
\fB                     {pos, {X :: integer(), Y :: integer()}} |\fR
\fB                     {sz, {W :: integer(), H :: integer()}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Constructor.

.PP
Use \fIwxDialog:showModal/1\fR to show the dialog.


.RE
.B
\fBsetDirectory(This, Directory) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          This :: wxFileDialog(),\fR
\fB                          Directory :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the default directory.


.RE
.B
\fBsetFilename(This, Setfilename) -> ok\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         This :: wxFileDialog(),\fR
\fB                         Setfilename :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the default filename.

.PP
In wxGTK this will have little effect unless a default directory has previously been set.


.RE
.B
\fBsetFilterIndex(This, FilterIndex) -> ok\fR
\fB                        when\fR
\fB                            This :: wxFileDialog(),\fR
\fB                            FilterIndex :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the default filter index, starting from zero.


.RE
.B
\fBsetMessage(This, Message) -> ok\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        This :: wxFileDialog(),\fR
\fB                        Message :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the message that will be displayed on the dialog.


.RE
.B
\fBsetPath(This, Path) -> ok\fR
\fB                 when This :: wxFileDialog(), Path :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the path (the combined directory and filename that will be returned when the dialog is dismissed).


.RE
.B
\fBsetWildcard(This, WildCard) -> ok\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         This :: wxFileDialog(),\fR
\fB                         WildCard :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the wildcard, which can contain multiple file types, for example: "BMP files (*.bmp)|*.bmp|GIF files (*.gif)|*.gif".

.PP
Note that the native Motif dialog has some limitations with respect to wildcards; see the Remarks section above.


.RE
